        "assistant": "In an AI/language-model context, **“token substrate”** and **“embedding space”** refer to different levels of representation.\n\n### Short version\n\n- **Token substrate** = the discrete symbolic layer: tokens such as `cat`, `##ing`, punctuation, or token IDs.\n- **Embedding space** = the continuous vector layer: numerical vectors representing those tokens in a high-dimensional space.\n\n### More concretely\n\nWhen text enters a language model, it is usually processed roughly like this:\n\n```text\nRaw text\n→ tokens\n→ token IDs\n→ embeddings / vectors\n→ model computation\n```\n\nThe **token substrate** is the layer where language has been broken into discrete units. For example:\n\n```text\n\"unbelievable\"\n→ [\"un\", \"believ\", \"able\"]\n```\n\nor possibly:\n\n```text\n\"unbelievable\"\n→ [token ID 403, token ID 9182, token ID 481]\n```\n\nThose tokens or token IDs are the substrate the model uses as its basic input units.\n\nThe **embedding space** is what happens after those discrete tokens are mapped into vectors:\n\n```text\ntoken ID 403 → [0.12, -0.45, 0.88, ...]\ntoken ID 9182 → [-0.03, 0.77, 0.21, ...]\n```\n\nThese vectors live in a high-dimensional continuous space. In that space, tokens with related meanings or uses may be closer together.\n\n### Key difference\n\n| Concept | Nature | Example |\n|---|---|---|\n| Token substrate | Discrete, symbolic | `\"cat\"`, `\"dog\"`, token ID `5721` |\n| Embedding space | Continuous, numerical | `[0.18, -0.04, 0.91, ...]` |\n\n### Analogy\n\nThink of the **token substrate** as letters or chess pieces: distinct units with identities.\n\nThink of the **embedding space** as a coordinate system where each piece is assigned a location based on its role, meaning, or usage.\n\nSo a token substrate defines **what the units are**.  \nAn embedding space defines **how those units are numerically represented and related** inside the model.\n\nOne important caveat: “token substrate” is not as standardized a technical term as “embedding space,” so its exact meaning can vary depending on the author.",
