        "user": "What is a token substrate?",
        "assistant": "A **token substrate** is the underlying layer or system that a token is built on and depends on.\n\nThe phrase is not always used in a single standardized way, but it usually means the **technical foundation that issues, records, transfers, and enforces rules for tokens**.\n\nFor example:\n\n- On Ethereum, the token substrate for many tokens is the Ethereum blockchain plus standards like **ERC-20** or **ERC-721**.\n- On Solana, it could be the Solana runtime plus the **SPL token** program.\n- In the Polkadot ecosystem, **Substrate** is also the name of a blockchain-building framework, so a “token substrate” might refer to a token system built using Substrate pallets such as balances, assets, or NFTs.\n\nA token substrate typically includes things like:\n\n- The ledger or database tracking ownership\n- Rules for minting, burning, and transferring tokens\n- Consensus or validation mechanisms\n- Smart contracts or runtime modules\n- APIs and wallet compatibility\n\nIn simpler terms: **if a token is like a digital asset, the token substrate is the platform or foundation that makes that asset work.**",
