        "assistant": "A **token substrate** generally means the **underlying system or infrastructure that tokens exist on and depend on**.\n\nThe term is not always used in one fixed way, but in tech/crypto contexts:\n\n- **Token** = a unit of value, access, identity, ownership, or utility.\n- **Substrate** = the base layer or foundation that supports something.\n\nSo a **token substrate** could refer to the platform, protocol, or ledger that makes tokens possible.\n\nExamples:\n\n- On Ethereum, the Ethereum blockchain is the substrate for ERC-20 tokens.\n- On Solana, Solana is the substrate for SPL tokens.\n- In the Polkadot ecosystem, **Substrate** is also the name of a blockchain-building framework, so a “token substrate” could mean the runtime or chain infrastructure used to create/manage tokens.\n- More broadly, a database, smart contract system, or payment network could act as a token substrate if it tracks token ownership and transfers.\n\nIn plain language:  \n**A token substrate is the foundation that stores, validates, and moves tokens.**",
